I've had my [VORON Trident][trident] for almost a year and I've run it for XXX hours.
Overall I'm happy with the printer but I've been itching to make some more mods to it.
Having finally finished the [VORON 0][] I now have a backup printer I can use to rescue myself if I screw up.

The mods I installed were:

1. [Inverted electronics][]
1. Replaced Stealthburner with the [A4T-toolhead][]

   I migrated from Tap to the [Beacon probe][].
   The toolhead also required me to replace the stock front idlers with the [Beefy idlers][].

1. Moved to an umbilical setup

   I used the [Nighthawk36 toolhead][] and moved the XY-endstops so I could remove the drag chains.

1. Beacon-friendly purge bucket mod

Okay, I admit; the biggest reason for the change is that it's fun to build and tinker...
To my defense the improvements are pretty nice.

